-- Greece Has Ratings Upgraded by Fitch on Distressed Debt Exchange
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2012-03-13T16:54:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/greece-has-ratings-upgraded-by-fitch-on-distressed-debt-exchange.html
  Greece  had its long-term foreign
and local currency issuer default ratings raised to B- with
stable outlooks from Restricted Default by Fitch Ratings, which
cited the 96 percent participation in the distressed debt
exchange.  The short-term foreign currency IDR has been upgraded to B
from C.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  